what are the symptoms if i have hepatitis c and i am pregnant you might get infected with hepatitis c virus and have no symptoms at all it is known to be the silent killer in some hep c infected patients they give symptoms which include abdominal pain mainly in the right upper quadrant of the abdomen feel tired depressed bowel problems including dark or pale stool diarrhoea or constipation unfortunately all the above mentioned symptoms mimic other medical problems this is why many patients infected with hepatitis c don't know that they are infected if you suspect that you might have contracted the disease you must have a test to check for hepatitis c antibodies good luck Hepatitis Diarrhea Coeliac disease Hepatitis C Cytomegalovirus Cirrhosis Stomach cancer Chronic fatigue syndrome Infectious mononucleosis Abdominal pain Crohn's disease Multiple sclerosis Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Medicine Autoimmune diseases Constipation Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome Prostate cancer Pneumonia Irritable bowel syndrome Porphyria Foodborne illness Fecal incontinence Malaria Obstetrics Colorectal cancer Endometriosis Diverticulosis Urinary incontinence Hepatitis B Hepatitis A Syphilis Group A streptococcal infection Diabetes mellitus Ovarian cancer Lupus erythematosus Ulcerative colitis Hypoglycemia Rabies Clinical depression Food allergy Primary biliary cirrhosis Spanish flu Common misconceptions about HIV and AIDS Sexually-transmitted infection Physical examination Diverticulitis Lassa fever Infectious disease Antiviral drug Marburg virus Budd-Chiari syndrome Traumatic brain injury Lyme disease Rheumatoid arthritis Breastfeeding Leptospirosis Asthma Common cold HIV test Parkinson's disease Glycogen storage disease type I Fibromyalgia AIDS reappraisal Dialysis Timeline of AIDS Toxoplasmosis Paracetamol Opioid Escherichia coli O157:H7 Lumbar puncture AIDS Diabetic neuropathy Poliomyelitis Dengue fever Bloating Gastroenteritis Q fever Appendicitis Angina M__ni__re___s disease Gastropar